overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The
  agent meticulously analyzed the existing codebase against these requirements,
  identifying several critical gaps. Subsequently, the agent proceeded to
  implement all high and medium priority missing features. This involved
  integrating a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with crucial safety warnings,
  developing detection logic for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and implementing a weighted scoring system for
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS. Furthermore, the agent enhanced the data
  export functionality by expanding the CSV to include all flattened
  questionnaire responses and introduced new questions for pain severity and
  chronic fatigue screening, complete with tailored recommendations. The
  implementation process included updating data types, validation schemas, UI
  components, and both the web and PDF report generation logic, significantly
  improving the application's adherence to the client's specifications.
